## Why this template exists

Sending an acknowledgement within 24h of an RFQ landing has two benefits:

1. **Signals professionalism** — many EPC firms go silent for a week before sending the proposal. A same-day ack differentiates SRE.
2. **Surfaces blocking questions early** — if the RFQ is missing critical info (process parameters, timeline expectations, scope ambiguity), better to ask now than discover in week 2 of drafting.

Don't overthink the ack — it's a 60-100 word email. The real work is in the proposal that follows.

---

## Operator review checklist before send

- [ ] RFQ number / customer reference verified
- [ ] Proposal ETA realistic (usually 5-15 business days; for tender format, can be 20+)
- [ ] Clarification questions (if any) are genuinely blocking — don't ask just to ask
- [ ] AIMS bridge contact CC'd if ME customer
- [ ] SRE internal owner CC'd (Ron for BD-led, Dharmesh for engineering-led, Chuck for US)
- [ ] Length 60–100 words
- [ ] No commitment to scope/price/timeline beyond what's confirmable

**Approved by**: ______________ **Date**: __________

