## Variants

### Variant A: tender format RFQ (Qatar Mushtaryat, Kuwait K-Tendering, Saudi Eitimad)

- Drop the personal greeting; use "Dear Sir/Madam,"
- Include tender reference number prominently
- Promise proposal by the tender deadline minus 2 business days (give yourself buffer)
- CC any local AIMS contact who handles tender registration

### Variant B: webinar follow-up RFQ

When the RFQ comes from someone who attended an SRE webinar:

- Open with: "Thanks for your follow-up after the SRE {{WEBINAR_TOPIC}} session on {{DATE}}."
- Reference the specific webinar topic that prompted the inquiry
- This is a warmer lead — acknowledge that

### Variant C: re-engagement RFQ (silent customer re-surfacing)

When a previously-silent customer (per R5 monitor) sends an RFQ:

- Open with reference to prior project: "Great to hear from you again — it's been since {{LAST_TOUCH_DATE}}, when we did {{PRIOR_PROJECT}}."
- Treat as warm; don't pretend it's a cold ack
- Loop in Ron or whoever owned the prior relationship
